132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1546
S.P. 630 In Senate, April 10, 2025
An Act to Require Recommendations from Study Commissions to
Be Printed as Legislative Documents
Reference to the Committee on State and Local Government suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BENNETT of Oxford.
Cosponsored by Representative GRAHAM of North Yarmouth and
Senator: ROTUNDO of Androscoggin, Representative: DUCHARME of Madison.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 3 MRSA §170-C is enacted to read:
3 §170-C. Reports of study commissions to Legislature
4 When a study commission is authorized to provide to the Legislature a report that
5 includes that study commission's recommendations, those recommendations must be
6 produced as an Act or resolve and are authorized for submission to the Legislature to which
7 the study commission is authorized to submit its report. All such legislation must be
8 referred to a committee of that Legislature and given a public hearing.
9 As used in this section, "study commission" means any group of individuals established
10 in an Act, resolve or joint order or by the Legislative Council whose duties include studying
11 and reporting to the Legislature on any matter or advising the Legislature on any matter.
12 As used in this section, "committee" means a joint standing committee or joint select
13 committee of the Legislature.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This bill requires that the recommendations of a study commission established by the
1166 Legislature be produced as legislation, submitted to the Legislature to which the study
1177 commission is required to submit its report, referred to a joint standing committee or joint
1188 select committee of the Legislature and given a public hearing.
